Associations between building technology and design. The concept of design and architectural solution. Getting acquainted with sample designs and analysis in seminar format. Students complete, under supervision, an architectural rough plan of a building with wooden structure: letter of explanation,  site plan, ground plan, elevations, section, specification of materials. Finalizing and presentation.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Provide basic knowledge and skills of architectural design, and understanding of architect's way of thinking as well as methodologies.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course students:
- can synthesize the understanding of a log builder and a carpenter of workability into designing a building;
- can apply their log and wood builing knowledge to designing a building;
- can design and finalize a small building with wooden structure according to preliminary design.
